<TITLE> Hannan Shah gets bail in 2 cases </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 25 (bdnews24.com) - The High Court Monday granted ad-interim bail to BNP leader, retired brigadier general ASM Hannan Shah, in two cases. Police arrested Hannan Shah and his son Shah Rezaul Hannan at their Mohakhali DOHS home May 14. An HC vacation bench of Justice Abdul Quddus and Justice Mohammad Abdul Awal granted the bail following appeals from Hannan Shah, an adviser to BNP chief Khaleda Zia. A bus owner, Noman, filed a Tk 1 lakh extortion case against Hannan with Kapashia Police Station on May 19. The other case was filed May 20 by one Haripada Brahmin with the same police station for allegedly grabbing a water body. Barrister Rafiqul Haque moved the bail petitions while deputy attorney general Abdur Rouf Mia stood against. bdnew
